    "all data is publicly available.",
    "IPFS uses content-addressable storage, which ensures that files are uniquely identified by their content rather than their location, thus enabling tamper-resistant data sharing since any change in content would result in a different file address (the address and the content are intimately linked).Overall, decentralised data sharing aligns with the principles and objectives outlined in the AI Act by promoting transparency and accountability.",
    "The AI Act places importance on data protection and security.",
    "Decentralised data sharing can enhance data tamper-proofness by utilising cryptographic techniques, access controls, and distributed storage mechanisms.",
    "By distributing data across a network of nodes, decentralised systems reduce the risk of a single point of failure."
